<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0592a2a4-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s1885"><num value="1885">§ 1885.</num><heading> Termination of proclamations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id0592a2a5-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s1885/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> Repealed. <ref href="/us/pl/93/618/tVI/s602/d">Pub. L. 93–618, title VI, § 602(d)</ref>, <date date="1975-01-03">Jan. 3, 1975</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/2072">88 Stat. 2072</ref>.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id0592a2a6-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s1885/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The President may at any time terminate, in whole or in part, any proclamation made under this subchapter.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0592a2a7-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/87/794/tII/s255">Pub. L. 87–794, title II, § 255</ref>, <date date="1962-10-11">Oct. 11, 1962</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/76/880">76 Stat. 880</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/93/618/tVI/s602/d">Pub. L. 93–618, title VI, § 602(d)</ref>, <date date="1975-01-03">Jan. 3, 1975</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/2072">88 Stat. 2072</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0592a2a8-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0592a2a9-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id0592a2aa-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1975—Subsec. (a). <ref href="/us/pl/93/618">Pub. L. 93–618</ref> struck out subsec. (a) which provided for termination of or withdrawal from trade agreements. See <ref href="/us/usc/t19/s2135">section 2135 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
